The paper deals with optimization of precoders and receive filters in a cellular system, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of Tomlinson-Harashima precoding (THP) and minimum mean squared error (MMSE) criterion also suggests a signal processing (cs.SI) component. The paper also mentions the use of adaptive algorithms, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or multimedia (cs.MM) depending on the specific techniques used.
